Definition: marked by good intentions though often producing unfortunate results
Example: a well-intentioned but clumsy waiter; a well-meaning but tactless fellow; the son's well-meaning efforts threw a singular chill upon the father's admirers- S.W.Maughm; blunt but well-meant criticism
Synonyms: well-meaning, well-meant, marked, by, good, intentions, though, often, producing, unfortunate, results, a, but, clumsy, waiter, tactless, fellow, the, son, s, efforts, threw, singular, chill, upon, father, admirers, -, S, W, Maughm, blunt, criticism
Category: adj.all
